data.text: @pretareporter You are quite a Handsome man

@mbraaad @LolabeanB @pretareporter How would you feel if I respond to your post to say your points are ridiculous and that your points tell me a lot about who you are as a person? Think about how words can impact " discussions" 
Have a good night. Peace.

@mbraaad @LolabeanB @pretareporter Labeling something someone says as ridiculous is not discussion. Its not trying to understand other peoples opinions, as you said in an earlier post. You said if I thought it was creepy it said more about me than them-also an insult. And I said I wasn't sure it was creepy.
@mbraaad @LolabeanB @pretareporter Haha! You said you wanted to have a discussion so I responded when the other person didn't. Now you insult me for stating my opinion. Oh well.
@LolabeanB @mbraaad @pretareporter Hollywood values are very very different.

@mbraaad @LolabeanB @pretareporter We don't know if it's creepy but it seems like maybe his life should be full of other interests and people. Maybe he could've tattooed something he liked about her- like if she liked roses he could've tattooed a rose. It would've been more private/ subtle.
@Linkus717 @LolabeanB @pretareporter Those reasons don't make it creepy? Sounds like he's really supportive of his sister.

@mbraaad @LolabeanB @pretareporter It's unusual for a brother to tattoo his sister's name on his arm. They seem to be close. He seems to attend a lot of her modeling events etc. It doesn't seem like he has a lot of other tattoos.

@LolabeanB @pretareporter Sorry you're not trying to have a discussion - don't know why you responded to the tweet in the first place. Thought that was a great part of twitter - the chance to understand opinions of others. I also have three brothers, just curious why you found it creepy.
@LolabeanB @pretareporter But what about it is creepy?
@LolabeanB @pretareporter People get names of celebs they've never met tattooed on their body, I think that's a hell of a lot creepier.
@pretareporter @THR Who cares? 17 teachers and children were killed and many more injured. Some perspective here.
